The paper deals with the problem of human pose estimation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning a model using both geometric and appearance distances, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). The method also involves building a structure of sub-trees using the Chow-Liu algorithm, which is commonly used in graphical models (cs.MM). Finally, the method handles occlusions, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO).
